  section#flex-grid
    h2 The Flex Grid
    p.
      A Flex Grid is simply a list of items arranged like blocks in a grid.
      It has the structure of a list in that all items share the same container
      (unlike tables where items are in different rows), while at the same time
      appearing like a table with rows and columns.
    p.
      The Flex Grid can be flexible and responsive, adjusting the number of
      columns based on screen size.
      By default, each item has full width.
      To achieve a grid-like appearance, set the widths of each item as necessary.
    p.
      The container must have the #[code.sg-c-Code .o-GridFlex] class
      (and, if necessary, class #[code .o-ListBare] to remove normal list styles).
      Each item must have the #[code.sg-c-Code .o-GridFlex__Item] class
      (and, if necessary, class #[code .o-Block]).
    p.
      See my article #[a(href="../blog/layout.html") The GridFlex Object].
